&quot;) ## Automated Line Performance Analysis cat(&quot;===================================
&quot;) ## =================================== cat(&quot;Ideal cycle time:&quot;, ideal_cycle_time, &quot;min/part
&quot;) ## Ideal cycle time: 1 min/part cat(&quot;Number of stations:&quot;, n_stations, &quot;
&quot;) ## Number of stations: 10 cat(&quot;Ideal production rate:&quot;, 60/ideal_cycle_time, &quot;parts/hour

&quot;) ## Ideal production rate: 60 parts/hour for(i in 1:nrow(scenarios)) { p &lt;- scenarios$Failure_Prob[i] T &lt;- scenarios$Repair_Time[i] # Line failure probability (any station) p_line &lt;- 1 - (1 - p)^n_stations # Actual cycle time Tp &lt;- ideal_cycle_time + p_line * T # Actual production rate Rp &lt;- 60 / Tp # Efficiency efficiency &lt;- (ideal_cycle_time / Tp) * 100 cat(sprintf(&quot;%s Performance:
